tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE marketing_strategies (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_name VARCHAR(50),
    test_group INT,
    conversion_rate FLOAT,
    revenue DECIMAL(10, 2)
)

CREATE TABLE test_results (
  test_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_name TEXT,
  test_date DATE,
  conversion_rate FLOAT,
  test_group TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE user_data (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  age INT,
  gender TEXT,
  location TEXT,
  test_group TEXT,
  converted BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE test_results (
  result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  group_id INT,
  metric_id INT,
  value DECIMAL,
  FOREIGN KEY (group_id) REFERENCES test_groups(group_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (metric_id) REFERENCES test_metrics(metric_id)
);

CREATE TABLE marketing_strategies (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_name VARCHAR(255),
    start_date TIMESTAMP,
    end_date TIMESTAMP,
    budget DECIMAL(10, 2),
    audience_size INT
)

CREATE TABLE test_groups (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    group_name VARCHAR(255),
    strategy_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (strategy_id) REFERENCES marketing_strategies(id)
)

CREATE TABLE test_results (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    group_id INT,
    conversion_rate DECIMAL(5, 2),
    revenue_generated DECIMAL(10, 2),
    test_date TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (group_id) REFERENCES test_groups(id)
)

CREATE TABLE test_logs (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    group_id INT,
    log_text TEXT,
    log_time TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (group_id) REFERENCES test_groups(id)
)

CREATE TABLE experiment_parameters (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    parameter_name VARCHAR(255),
    parameter_value TEXT,
    strategy_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (strategy_id) REFERENCES marketing_strategies(id)
)
